"O - I'm a pretty big fan of IBB and love the moderate sweet with the coffee bitter. I opened this at about 51 degrees, so it wasn't like I needed it to warm up to get those cherries: ultimately, I actually had hoped it was just a bit sweeter and a bit more cherry-forward; what I'll do in the future is a side-by-side with regular IBB: that might ultimately help to discern that cherry flavor a bit more. It's a damn good beer nonetheless."
